<title>GERMANY: Siemens-Nixdorf sees service profit loss.</title>
<headline>Siemens-Nixdorf sees service profit loss.</headline>
<dateline>FRANKFURT 1997-07-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>Siemens Nixdorf Informationssysteme AG expected its service unit to lose about 58 million marks in 1996/97 and then turn a profit of 30 million marks next year, business daily Handelsblatt reported on Monday.</p>
<p>SNI, a unit of industrial group Siemens AG, planned to restructure its product service unit into five comapnies that could be operated as more flexible, middle-sized companies.</p>
<p>SNI has service revenue of 350 million marks in the business year that ended September 30.</p>
<p>Siemens was expected to release nine-month results on Monday.</p>
<p>-- Bonn Newsroom, +49-228 26097150</p>
